WEBVTT

00:00.601 --> 00:02.168
<i>, here's what you missed on
Glee: Quinn was dating Sam,</i>

00:02.235 --> 00:04.037
<i>but then she kissed Finn, so
Santana told Sam, and now</i>

00:04.104 --> 00:05.805
<i>they've started dating.
You are Biebalicious.</i>

00:05.873 --> 00:08.141
<i>Will's not dating anyone and
says he's over Emma, but it</i>

00:08.209 --> 00:09.676
<i>seems like he's still got a
thing for her, even though
she's married.</i>

00:09.743 --> 00:11.511
<i>Kurt's really into Blaine,
and Blaine likes Kurt,</i>

00:11.579 --> 00:13.146
<i>but he says he just wants to
stay friends.</i>

00:13.214 --> 00:15.048
<i>And that's what you missed
on Glee.</i>

00:16.884 --> 00:18.585
(school bell rings)
Figgins,

00:18.652 --> 00:20.353
you wanted to see me?

00:20.421 --> 00:21.621
William, we have an epidemic
on our hands.

00:21.689 --> 00:24.090
Head lice?
Worse. Giggle juice.

00:24.158 --> 00:25.725
I-I'm sorry. What?

00:25.793 --> 00:27.060
Alcohol, William.

00:27.127 --> 00:28.628
The wet devil.

00:28.696 --> 00:29.762
Our children

00:29.830 --> 00:31.698
are so brazen,
they are showing up

00:31.765 --> 00:32.999
to school wasted.

00:33.067 --> 00:34.934
And not wasted
on learning, Will.

00:35.002 --> 00:36.269
Wasted on booze.

00:36.337 --> 00:38.471
Why, just this week,
we've had five suspensions

00:38.539 --> 00:40.673
for intoxication
on school grounds.

00:40.741 --> 00:42.242
(pounding on window)
Figgins!

00:42.309 --> 00:43.743
You rock!

00:43.811 --> 00:45.278
Yeah, man!

00:45.346 --> 00:47.680
Six suspensions.

00:47.748 --> 00:49.182
I-I don't get it.

00:49.250 --> 00:50.984
Drinking's never been a problem
at this school.

00:51.051 --> 00:52.585
That's because there are
new alcoholic beverages

00:52.653 --> 00:53.886
targeted to kids, Will.

00:53.954 --> 00:55.521
Just listen
to the radio.

00:55.589 --> 00:58.858
Pop music now glorifies
binge drinking.

00:58.926 --> 01:00.059
Just listen to any hit

01:00.127 --> 01:03.229
by pop sensation
Ke-dollar-sign-ha.

01:03.297 --> 01:05.230
Oh. You-You mean Ke$ha?

01:05.299 --> 01:07.100
We must do something
to protect our children, Will.

01:07.167 --> 01:08.935
I-I totally agree.

01:09.003 --> 01:10.570
How-How can I help?

01:10.638 --> 01:12.572
I have decided to make this week

01:12.640 --> 01:13.906
Alcohol Awareness Week

01:13.974 --> 01:15.074
at McKinley.

01:15.142 --> 01:16.476
I have contacted
Kitty Dukakis,

01:16.543 --> 01:18.111
who will be
the guest speaker

01:18.178 --> 01:21.214
at an assembly where your
Glee Club will perform a song

01:21.282 --> 01:23.049
highlighting the dangers

01:23.117 --> 01:24.050
of teenage drinking.

01:25.552 --> 01:26.719
Can I count on you, William?

01:32.026 --> 01:33.259
(school bell ringing)

01:33.327 --> 01:34.894
WILL:
Emma?
Hi.

01:34.962 --> 01:36.262
Enough with us
not being friends.

01:36.330 --> 01:38.131
Look, I heard through the
grapevine that you and Carl

01:38.198 --> 01:39.265
started looking
for a tract house together,

01:39.333 --> 01:40.833
and I just wanted to say

01:40.901 --> 01:43.136
that I'm genuinely
happy for you.

01:43.203 --> 01:44.604
Thank you.

01:44.672 --> 01:46.472
(chuckling)
That's really sweet.

01:46.540 --> 01:48.308
Two-slicer.
(laughs)

01:48.375 --> 01:50.009
Do you want to catch up?

01:50.077 --> 01:52.011
Yeah. Sure.

01:52.079 --> 01:53.913
(clears throat)

01:53.981 --> 01:55.448
How have you been?

01:55.516 --> 01:57.684
Busy. Yeah.

01:57.751 --> 01:59.052
Glee Club's gearing up
for Regionals...

01:59.119 --> 02:01.287
I, um, love hearing
about the Glee Club,

02:01.355 --> 02:02.922
but I'm actually more
interested in you.

02:02.990 --> 02:04.791
You know, how
you're doing.
Me? Uh...

02:04.858 --> 02:06.492
Are you dating anybody?

02:06.560 --> 02:08.227
No.

02:08.294 --> 02:10.530
No?

02:10.597 --> 02:12.365
Maybe you should.

02:12.433 --> 02:14.067
You know,
Ella, I think

02:14.134 --> 02:15.902
Will should really concentrate
on his treatment

02:15.969 --> 02:17.170
before he tries another
relationship

02:17.237 --> 02:19.238
with an early hominid,
even a human female.

02:19.306 --> 02:21.841
Treatment?
Alcoholics Anonymous, Will.

02:21.909 --> 02:23.876
I suggest you
pre-emptively check

02:23.944 --> 02:26.512
into rehab,
as you are a future alcoholic.

02:26.580 --> 02:28.214
I mean, come on.

02:28.282 --> 02:30.216
Look where you are.
You're coaching a Glee Club

02:30.284 --> 02:32.285
that can only beat
choirs of old people.

02:32.353 --> 02:35.221
You're rehashing the details
of your failed marriage

02:35.289 --> 02:38.558
with the very lemur
who rejected the bestial horror

02:38.625 --> 02:39.826
of your craven sexual advances.

02:39.893 --> 02:42.595
And when my Glee Club
crushes you at Regionals,

02:42.663 --> 02:46.099
well, the last ounce of meaning
will drain from your life,

02:46.166 --> 02:47.567
and you will turn to drink.

02:47.634 --> 02:48.801
I don't get it. How is it

02:48.869 --> 02:50.203
that you're now
coaching a Glee Club?

02:50.270 --> 02:52.472
I was so inspired by my stint
in the Glee Club,

02:52.539 --> 02:54.474
that I took the trip
to Westvale,

02:54.541 --> 02:55.708
and I volunteered my help.

02:55.776 --> 02:57.477
Unfortunately,
the chipper homosexual

02:57.544 --> 02:59.045
who coaches Aural Intensity

02:59.113 --> 03:00.880
had a terrible fall
down the stairs.

03:00.948 --> 03:02.782
(epic music plays)

03:05.252 --> 03:07.353
I'm okay. Don't worry.

03:10.557 --> 03:11.691
(grunting)

03:11.759 --> 03:12.992
Not to be alarmed.

03:13.060 --> 03:15.528
Doctors say he will be fine.
Provided they can get

03:15.596 --> 03:16.896
the swelling in his brain
under control.

03:16.964 --> 03:19.031
Okay, sorry. I still
don't understand.

03:19.099 --> 03:21.267
How can the school let
you coach Aural Intensity?

03:21.335 --> 03:23.002
Newsflash, Amelda.

03:23.070 --> 03:25.338
There's no one lining up
to coach Glee Clubs

03:25.406 --> 03:27.240
because it's a sucky job
for losers.

03:27.307 --> 03:30.042
But there was an opening,
and I am a champion.

03:30.110 --> 03:32.378
Oh, Will.
Here's the book by Bill W.,

03:32.446 --> 03:35.181
outlining the 12 steps
of Alcoholics Anonymous.

03:35.249 --> 03:36.983
I can't wait for you
to start climbing those steps,

03:37.050 --> 03:38.217
because when you get to the top,

03:38.285 --> 03:40.686
I'm gonna knock you back down.

03:43.190 --> 03:44.624
