Hey.

04:23.330 --> 04:24.430
Yo.

04:24.498 --> 04:25.498
How's the song-
writing going?

04:25.566 --> 04:28.100
Hey. It's going amazing.

04:28.168 --> 04:30.102
I think I might have
a really big hit here,

04:30.170 --> 04:31.270
which is why
I wanted you to come by.

04:31.338 --> 04:32.738
I-I want you to hear it.

04:32.806 --> 04:34.373
Oh. Yeah. Cool.

04:34.441 --> 04:36.309
Come here.

04:42.483 --> 04:43.349
(chuckles)

04:46.553 --> 04:47.687
What was that for?

04:47.754 --> 04:49.121
To break the tension.

04:49.189 --> 04:51.557
We were boyfriend
and girlfriend, Finn.

04:51.625 --> 04:53.025
It's silly for us to pretend

04:53.093 --> 04:54.494
like we aren't comfortable
around each other.

04:54.561 --> 04:56.596
Yeah. Totally.

04:56.663 --> 04:58.498
And I know that we have
some unresolved feelings,

04:58.565 --> 05:02.268
but like my two new role models
Carole King and Gerry Goffin,

05:02.336 --> 05:03.603
I think it's important
that we just

05:03.670 --> 05:06.706
put them aside and stay
focused on our mission

05:06.773 --> 05:08.908
which is just
to write an amazing song

05:08.976 --> 05:10.209
