obviously conflicted,

26:55.257 --> 26:56.724
and if he
turns out not

26:56.792 --> 26:59.527
to be gay, well, then I guess I
will have done you a favor.

26:59.595 --> 27:03.064
And I'm doing you a favor
by telling you that Blaine

27:03.132 --> 27:06.834
is the first of a long line
of conflicted men that

27:06.902 --> 27:08.203
you will date
that will later

27:08.270 --> 27:10.405
turn out to be only
thmost flaming of homosexuals.

27:10.472 --> 27:12.540
Blaine and I have
a lot in common.

27:12.608 --> 27:15.877
A sentiment expressed
by many a hag about many a gay.

27:15.945 --> 27:18.213
Look, I don't doubt
that you and Blaine

27:18.280 --> 27:22.150
would have a jolly good time
shopping at Burberry

27:22.218 --> 27:23.751
and arguing
who would make

27:23.819 --> 27:25.253
the better Rum Tum Tugger--

27:25.321 --> 27:27.121
I don't dispute that--

27:27.189 --> 27:29.657
but there's something you
and Blaine'll never have...

27:29.725 --> 27:31.326
and that's chemistry.

27:33.362 --> 27:35.730
Fine.

27:35.798 --> 27:37.565
Then I'm gonna
prove you wrong.

27:37.633 --> 27:39.067
I'm gonna take

27:39.134 --> 27:41.202
the beer goggles off, and
I'm gonna kiss him sober.

27:41.270 --> 27:44.272
And if the spark is still
there, then I'm taking you

27:44.340 --> 27:47.976
to your bakery of choice for a
piping hot slice of humble pie.

27:52.629 --> 27:54.396
(Beiste laughs)

27:54.464 --> 27:56.765
Whoa! Whoa, whoa,
easy, partner.

27:56.833 --> 27:58.901
(slurring): Can I get
you something to drink?

27:58.969 --> 28:00.703
Oh, no, no, no, no.

28:00.770 --> 28:02.738
Taxi's waiting.
All right.

28:02.806 --> 28:05.007
(exhales)
H-H-How are you not drunk?

28:05.075 --> 28:06.876
We drank exactly
the same amount.

28:06.943 --> 28:08.644
I got a hollow leg.

28:08.712 --> 28:10.579
(laughs)
You got a hollow leg!

28:10.647 --> 28:12.348
You gonna be okay?

28:12.415 --> 28:13.916
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Yeah?

28:13.984 --> 28:17.052
(grunts) I just... just
got to grade some papers

28:17.120 --> 28:18.587
and... I'm still looking

28:18.655 --> 28:20.923
for a song for the kids to sing

28:20.991 --> 28:23.659
at the Alcohol
Awareness Assembly.

28:23.727 --> 28:25.027
Oh...
Yes, uh...

28:25.095 --> 28:27.630
The kids
want to sing a Ke$ha song...

28:27.697 --> 28:31.867
but, uh, it just makes drinking
seem like a lot of fun.

28:31.935 --> 28:33.602
<i>Sometimes it is fun.</i>

28:33.670 --> 28:35.671
Exactly.
(chuckles)

28:35.739 --> 28:37.139
Like tonight.

28:37.207 --> 28:39.808
That's the most fun I've had
in a really long time.

28:39.876 --> 28:41.777
I mean, we were careful.
Mm-hmm.

28:41.845 --> 28:43.445
We didn't drive.
Mm, yeah.

28:43.513 --> 28:44.647
What's wrong with that?

28:44.714 --> 28:45.681
Nothin'.

28:45.749 --> 28:47.316
Nothin's wrong with that.

28:47.384 --> 28:49.385
Except we're not
teenagers anymore, Will.

28:51.087 --> 28:52.354
You know?

28:52.422 --> 28:54.089
The way I see it,

28:54.157 --> 28:55.624
you can't just
lecture kids.

28:55.692 --> 28:57.860
I mean, we can't stop
them from drinking

28:57.928 --> 28:59.795
if that's what
they're gonna do.

28:59.863 --> 29:01.597
I mean, the best
we can do

29:01.665 --> 29:04.033
is make them aware of
the dangers and just...

29:04.100 --> 29:05.234
hope they're
smart enough

29:05.302 --> 29:08.604
to make a good
decision on their own.

29:08.672 --> 29:10.539
(laughing)

29:12.208 --> 29:14.376
Nut. All right, buddy,
I'm out of here.

29:14.444 --> 29:15.811
Okay.
Don't get up.

29:15.879 --> 29:17.246
(grunts)
I'm not...
(slurred muttering)

29:17.314 --> 29:19.248
All right, hey.
Yes?

29:19.316 --> 29:21.650
You just make sure you
drink lots of water.

29:21.718 --> 29:23.185
Okay?
Mwa!

29:23.253 --> 29:24.954
I love you.

29:25.021 --> 29:26.622
Right back at you.

29:26.690 --> 29:28.357
Yay, happy face.

29:28.425 --> 29:30.259
Okay.

29:30.327 --> 29:31.961
(belches)

29:32.028 --> 29:34.430
That was a valiant effort.

29:34.497 --> 29:36.098
You get a A-plus.

29:36.166 --> 29:37.066
That's how I roll.

29:37.133 --> 29:40.102
I don't even know who you are.

29:45.041 --> 29:46.542
Oh, what the hell?

29:49.045 --> 29:51.847
Hey, there...

29:51.915 --> 29:53.782
sexy lady. (chuckles)

29:53.850 --> 29:56.185
I know it's late.

29:56.252 --> 29:59.288
And... I know you're taken,

29:59.356 --> 30:01.457
and I've had
a couple drinks, but...

30:03.393 --> 30:07.663
<i>...there's something I r-really,
really want to say to you.</i>

30:07.731 --> 30:09.565
(school bell rings)

30:11.067 --> 30:12.568
William!

30:12.635 --> 30:14.903
Can't wait to see what your
New Directions are planning

30:14.971 --> 30:16.939
for the assembly.
I know we've had issues

30:17.007 --> 30:19.274
with your kids performing
in front of the school,

30:19.342 --> 30:21.877
but I have a really good feeling
about this one.

30:21.945 --> 30:23.312
(whispers):
Why are you screaming?

30:23.380 --> 30:24.947
I'm not screaming.
Are you okay?

30:25.015 --> 30:27.716
Oh... wow, your cologne
is just really strong.

30:27.784 --> 30:30.019
It's Drakar Noir!

30:30.086 --> 30:31.620
Emma.
(laughs)
Ooh...

30:31.688 --> 30:33.822
Will, you look terrible.

30:33.890 --> 30:35.624
Considering how
much I drank,

30:35.692 --> 30:37.292
I think I'm lucky
to be alive.

30:37.360 --> 30:39.161
(laughs)
Although I kind of
wish I was dead.

30:39.229 --> 30:41.196
I am so embarrassed.

30:41.264 --> 30:43.665
Why? I mean, besides
the fact that you drank

30:43.733 --> 30:46.335
like a frat boy
and you're well
into your 30's.

30:46.403 --> 30:48.904
Please don't
make me say it.
Sorry?

30:48.972 --> 30:51.940
I don't even remember
half the things I said to you.
I-I'm not following.

30:52.008 --> 30:53.642
I-I drunk-dialed you last night.

30:53.710 --> 30:55.277
No, you didn't.

30:55.345 --> 30:57.246
I mean, I didn't get
a single message.

30:57.313 --> 30:59.848
What would you have said that
you'd be embarrassed about?

30:59.916 --> 31:00.983
Nothing.

31:01.051 --> 31:02.785
(school bell rings)
(both laughing)

31:02.852 --> 31:04.286
I-I-I... This
must have been

31:04.354 --> 31:06.755
a really elaborate, uh,
booze dream, yeah.

31:06.823 --> 31:08.590
SUE:
It's time, Will.

31:08.658 --> 31:10.626
I've arranged to have you
committed for 48 hours,

31:10.693 --> 31:12.061
and it's not
gonna be easy.

31:12.128 --> 31:14.797
Those state institutions
tend to turn the fire hose

31:14.864 --> 31:16.565
on patients going
through the D.T.'s,

31:16.633 --> 31:18.500
but at this point,
I have no other option

31:18.568 --> 31:19.601
but a forced intervention.

31:19.669 --> 31:22.604
Sue, I do not have
a drinking problem.

31:22.672 --> 31:24.506
Really? Then what's with
the Corey Hart imitation?

31:24.574 --> 31:25.541
(sighs)

31:25.608 --> 31:27.709
Will, I'm trying to save you.

31:27.777 --> 31:30.312
Why? All you ever want
to do is destroy me.

31:30.346 --> 31:33.182
Yeah, well, it's kind of like
nursing a P.O.W. back to health

31:33.249 --> 31:35.384
so he's at his strongest
when you torture him to death.

31:35.452 --> 31:36.985
(groans)

31:37.053 --> 31:38.487
All right, Will,
you had your chance

31:38.555 --> 31:39.988
to do this the easy way.

31:40.056 --> 31:41.790
KURT: Souffle is all
about the whites.

31:41.858 --> 31:44.726
If you get yolk in it
or you don't let it
stiffen properly

31:44.794 --> 31:46.628
then you might as well
be making pancakes.

31:46.696 --> 31:49.465
All right. You think the one
we already made is ready yet?

31:49.532 --> 31:50.699
I hope so.

31:50.767 --> 31:52.734
All right, let's check it out.

31:52.802 --> 31:54.536
Here we go.

31:54.604 --> 31:56.238
Ta-da.
(sighs)

31:56.306 --> 31:58.440
You didn't leave
enough room in the
dish to let it rise.

31:58.508 --> 32:00.776
Hey, I'm sorry-- why are
you being so hard on me?

32:00.844 --> 32:03.512
I would've been happy
with you teaching me
to make toast.

32:03.580 --> 32:06.448
I'm sorry, Dad, I know
this is supposed to be
bonding time, but...

32:06.516 --> 32:07.916
it's Blaine.

32:07.984 --> 32:10.552
He's interested...
in Rachel.

32:12.021 --> 32:14.022
I'm confused;
I thought he was gay, too.

32:14.090 --> 32:15.424
Oh, he is, he is.

32:15.492 --> 32:18.660
He's just...
experimenting.

32:18.728 --> 32:21.230
(laughs)
Yeah. He's not the only one.

32:21.297 --> 32:22.698
What does that mean?

32:22.765 --> 32:24.600
Look, I need you to ask me

32:24.667 --> 32:26.435
before you have
someone sleep over.

32:26.503 --> 32:28.137
We-we were fullylothed
the entire time,

32:28.204 --> 32:31.240
and Blaine was too drunk to
drive, so I let him crash here.

32:31.307 --> 32:32.441
I was being responsible.

32:32.509 --> 32:33.842
Wait a minute,
you kids are drinking now?

32:33.910 --> 32:35.644
Finn and I didn't have any.

32:35.712 --> 32:37.346
If that's what
you're worried about.

32:37.413 --> 32:38.647
No. I'm worried

32:38.715 --> 32:41.950
about you being
inappropriate
in my house.

32:42.018 --> 32:44.853
And if Puckerman had
a sleepover with Finn,

32:44.921 --> 32:46.722
would that be inappropriate?

32:46.789 --> 32:48.690
That's different.
Because they
wouldn't have sex?

32:48.758 --> 32:53.128
No, I would never allow Finn
to have a girl sleep over

32:53.196 --> 32:54.763
in his bed.

32:54.831 --> 32:56.732
But would it make you
uncomfortable if he did?

32:56.799 --> 32:58.700
Hey, when have
I been uncomfortable

32:58.768 --> 33:00.969
<i>with you being gay?
So it's not being gay
that upsets you,</i>

33:01.037 --> 33:02.337
it's just me acting on it.

33:02.405 --> 33:05.140
I don't know what two guys do
when they're together.

33:05.208 --> 33:07.876
<i>You know, I sat through
that whole Brokeback Mountain.</i>

33:07.944 --> 33:09.444
From what I gather,

33:09.512 --> 33:11.246
